Search and rescue teams resumed operations on Monday morning after a seven-year-old boy went missing in the uMvoti River in KwaZulu-Natal. JOHANNESBURG - The father of the seven-year-old boy who went missing in the uMvoti River in KwaZulu-Natal on Sunday says that he was with his son when he slipped into the water. Search and rescue teams resumed operations on Monday morning. "I don't know how I can explain it, because he went once inside the water and reappeared once from the water and after that he disappeared," said the father. READ: Search for missing KZN boy intensifies He said he tried to get inside the river but couldn't find his son. This is one of many drowning instances in the area.